OL,6,F"However, after examination of all
OL,7,Frelevant evidence, including radio
OL,8,Ftransmissions, body worn video and
OL,9,Fother video footage of the incident, I
OL,10,Fwas of the view that the arresting
OL,11,Fpolice officer had not responded to
OL,12,Fthe unfolding events in line with an
OL,13,Forder to treat the gathering with
OL,14,Fsensitivity."
OL,16,FMrs Anderson said she had submitted a
OL,17,Ffile to the Public Prosecution Service
OL,18,F(PPS) for a decision on whether two
OL,19,Fofficers who attended the scene should
OL,20,Fbe prosecuted for assault.
